{{Infobox football league season | competition = [[Eredivisie|Netherl. Football Championship]] | season = 1895-96 | winners = [[HVV Den Haag]] (2nd title) | prevseason = [[1894–95 Netherlands Football League Championship|1894–95]] | nextseason = [[1896–97 Netherlands Football League Championship|1896–97]] }}
The '''[[Eredivisie|Netherlands Football League Championship]] 1895/1896''' was contested by seven teams from the cities [[Amsterdam]], [[The Hague]], [[Haarlem]], [[Rotterdam]] and [[Wageningen]]. The teams participated in the competition that would later be called ''Eerste Klasse West''. But since the western football district of the Netherlands was the only one to have a competition at the time, it could be regarded as a national championship. This was also the reason that [[GVC (football club)|Go Ahead Wageningen]] participated, as they would later play in the eastern division. [[HVV Den Haag]] won the championship.
==New entrant== *[[HV Victoria|Victoria Rotterdam]] returned after one season of absence
