'''Maria Yuryevna Tolkacheva''' ({{lang-ru|Мария Юрьевна Толкачёва}}; born {{birth date|1997|8|8|df=yes}}) is a Russian group [[rhythmic gymnast]]. She is the [[2016 Summer Olympics|2016 Olympics]] Group all-around champion and the [[2015 World Rhythmic Gymnastics Championships|2015 World]] Group all-around champion.

== Career ==
Tolkacheva became an official member of the Russian national group in the 2014 season, she was member of the Russian group that won group all-around gold at the [[2014 Rhythmic Gymnastics European Championships|2014 European Championships]] in [[Baku]], [[Azerbaijan]] and at the [[2014 World Rhythmic Gymnastics Championships|2014 World Championships]] in [[Izmir]], where they finished 4th in group all-around and won gold in 2Ribbon + 3Balls.

In 2015, Tolkacheva and the Russian group competed at the inaugural [[2015 European Games]], taking gold in group all-around and 5 ribbons.<ref>{{cite web|title=I. EUROPEAN GAMES 2015 - RHYTHMIC GYMNASTICS|url=http://www.gymmedia.com/Rhythmic-Gymnastics/I-EUROPEAN-GAMES-2015-RHYTHMIC-GYMNASTICS|publisher=Gymmedia|date= |accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref> They ended their season by winning gold in Group all-around at the [[2015 World Rhythmic Gymnastics Championships|2015 World Championships]] in [[Stuttgart]], Germany, as well as gold in 6 Clubs/2 Hoops and silver in 5 Ribbons. At these Worlds, [[Russia]] finally regained the gold medal in the all-around competition, after eight years, the last time they won the group competition was at the [[2007 World Rhythmic Gymnastics Championships|2007 World Championships]] held in [[Patras]], Greece.

In 2016, Tolkacheva and the Russian group won group gold at the [[2016 Rhythmic Gymnastics European Championships|2016 European Championships]] in [[Holon]], [[Israel]]. On August 19–21, Tolkacheva was member of the golden winning Russian group (together with [[Anastasia Maksimova]], [[Anastasiia Tatareva]], [[Anastasia Bliznyuk]], [[Vera Biryukova]]) that won gold at the [[Gymnastics at the 2016 Summer Olympics - Women's rhythmic group all-around|2016 Summer Olympics]] held in [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Rhythmic gymnastics: Russia wins fifth successive team gold|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-olympics-rio-rgymnastics-w-team-idUSKCN10W0MP|publisher=Reuters|date= |accessdate=21 August 2016}}</ref>

