{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2016}} {{Use British English|date=October 2016}} {{Infobox venue | name = Parkneuk Sports Stadium | nickname = | image = | location = Milton Street, [[Motherwell]], [[North Lanarkshire]], [[Scotland]] | coordinates = 55°47'50.9"N 3°59'30.0"W | opened = 1949 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = 1972 | owner = | operator = | surface = }}
'''Parkneuk Sports Stadium''' was a greyhound racing and speedway track on Milton Street, [[Motherwell]], [[North Lanarkshire]], [[Scotland]].
The track was situated west of Milton Street and built in 1949 on the site of the Parkneuk Colliery pit numbers 1 and 2.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.old-maps.co.uk/#/Map/275239/657816/13/101329|title=OS Plan 1958|publisher=old-maps.co.uk}}</ref> It also went by the name of 'The Stadium' and the Lanarkshire Speedway and Sports Stadium. The greyhound racing was independent (unaffiliated to a governing body) and opened on 15 October. The [[Motherwell Eagles|Lanarkshire Eagles]] speedway team also rode at the venue from 1950-1954.<ref>{{cite book|last=Barnes|first=Julia|title=Daily Mirror Greyhound Fact File|pages =34–97|year=1988|publisher=Ringpress Books|isbn=0-948955-15-5}}</ref> It competed for many years with another independent greyhound track called the [[Clyde Valley Greyhound Track]] at the bottom of Airbles Road.
Greyhound racing ended in 1972 and the site today consists of the Daisy Park Community Centre and Our Lady of Good Aid Cathedral Primary School.
