'''Thurles Racecourse''' is a [[horse racing]] venue in the town of [[Thurles]], [[County Tipperary]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]] which stages [[National Hunt]] racing. Racing has taken place at Thurles since 1732 when a three-day festival took place at the venue.
The course is located 1.5km west of the town centre. The course is an oval right handed track of one and a quarter miles with 6 flights of hurdles and 7 steeplechase fences in each circuit with a steep uphill finish.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.goracing.ie/HRI/Whats-On/Racecourses/Thurles/ |title=Course Profile|date=|work=Go Racing|accessdate=19 September 2012 }}</ref>
